aS'President Trump clearly inherited an economy on the upswing, according to the 2016 Census report, with income, health coverage and poverty levels having all improved in the past two years.'
p2402
aS'The question is whether his administration and the Republican-controlled Congress will sustain the momentum, or even reverse it.'
p2403
aS'The  ,  , showed median income, adjusted for inflation, grew by 3.2 percent from 2015 to 2106, to $59,039, as employers added jobs and hours and even, in some cases, gave raises.'
p2404
aS'At the same time, the poverty rate decreased by 0.8 percentage points, or 2.5 million people, to 12.7 percent.'
p2405
aS'Both measures are now at or near their prerecession levels in 2007, a hard-fought recovery.'
p2406
aS'On health care, the data show that the ranks of the uninsured fell last year by 900,000 people, to an all-time low of 8.8 percent of the population.'
p2407
aS'The decline is a result of the Affordable Care Act, or Obamacare.'
p2408
aS'The 32 states and District of Columbia that participate in the A.C.A.\xe2\x80\x99s expansion of Medicaid for low-income families had larger declines in their uninsured populations than states that do not participate.'
p2409
aS'Massachusetts, for example, a pioneer in broad coverage, has the lowest uninsured rate in the nation, 2.5 percent, while Texas, which rejected Medicaid expansion, has the highest, 16.6 percent.'
p2410
aS'The data also show the success of federal safety-net programs.'
p2411
aS'If not for tax credits for low-income workers, an additional 8.2 million people would have been classified as poor last year.'
p2412
aS'Similarly, food stamps and low-income housing aid lifted 3.6 million and 3.1 million people, respectively, out of poverty last year.'
p2413
aS'For all the improvement, however, broad prosperity remains elusive.'
p2414
