p3276
aS'Phil Robertson of Human Rights Watch said satellite images showed about half of all Rohingya villages had been torched and it was time that Suu Kyi, the government and military faced the fact that the security forces "shoot and kill who they want" and burn villages.'
p3277
aS'Amnesty International said there was "overwhelming evidence" the security forces were engaged in ethnic cleansing.'
p3278
aS'"While it was positive to hear Aung San Suu Kyi condemn human rights violations in Rakhine state, she is still silent about the role of the security forces," the group said.'
