aS'Toys \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us Inc, the largest U.S. toy store chain, filed for bankruptcy protection late Monday, the latest sign of turmoil in the retail industry that is caught in a viselike grip of online shopping and discount chains.'
p3533
aS'The Chapter 11 filing is among the largest ever by a specialty retailer and casts doubt over the future of its about 1,600 stores and 64,000 employees.'
p3534
aS'It comes just as Toys \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us is gearing up for the holiday shopping season, which accounts for the bulk of its sales.'
p3535
aS'"While today\xe2\x80\x99s decision does not necessarily mean it is game over for Toys \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us, it brings to a close a turbulent chapter in the iconic company\xe2\x80\x99s history," said Neil Saunders, managing director of GlobalData Retail.'
p3536
aS'Toys \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us received a commitment for over $3 billion in debtor-in-possession financing from lenders including a JPMorgan-led bank syndicate and certain existing lenders, said the Wayne, New Jersey-based company, which also operates the Babies \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us chain.'
p3537
aS'The financing, subject to court approval, reassures its suppliers they will get paid for their Lego building blocks and Barbie dolls that are being shipped for the holiday season.'
p3538
aS'"We expect that the financial constraints that have held us back will be addressed in a lasting and effective way," Chief Executive Dave Brandon said.'
p3539
aS'"Together with our investors, our objective is to work with our debtholders and other creditors to restructure the $5 billion of long-term debt on our balance sheet".'
p3540
aS'Its Canadian unit intends to seek protection in parallel proceedings under the Companies\xe2\x80\x99 Creditors Arrangement Act (CCAA) in the Ontario Superior Court of Justice, Toys \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us said in a statement.'
p3541
aS'Operations outside of the United States and Canada, including about 255 licensed stores and joint venture partnerships in Asia, which are separate entities, are not part of the bankruptcy proceedings, Toys \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us said.'
p3542
aS'The company\xe2\x80\x99s Toys \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us and Babies \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us stores and e-commerce sites around the world are open for business, it said.'
p3543
aS'The company is saddled with debt from a $6.6 billion buyout in 2005 led by KKR & Co LP ( ) and Bain Capital LP, together with real estate investment trust Vornado Realty Trust ( ).'
p3544
aS'Toys \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us has bonds coming due next year that have lost half their value this month, according to Thomson Reuters data, as investors have grown concerned about a possible bankruptcy.'
p3545
aS'The company opened a temporary store in New York City\xe2\x80\x99s Times Square this year to capture more holiday shoppers, almost two years after it closed its flagship store barely a block away, driven out by high rents.'
p3546
aS'"Vendors have cut them off based upon the rumors of the filing which has not been refuted," said Jay Indyke, a bankruptcy attorney with the Cooley law firm.'
p3547
aS'With assets of $6.9 billion based on its most recent annual report, it\xe2\x80\x99s the second-largest retail bankruptcy, trailing the filing in 2002 by Kmart, which had $14.6 billion in assets, according to research firm Bankruptcydata.com.'
p3548
aS'More than a dozen significant retail chains have filed for bankruptcy this year.'
p3549
aS'Among them were Perfumania Inc, apparel chains rue21 Inc and Gymboree Corp, discount shoe chain Payless Holdings LLC and designer clothing chain BCBG Max Azria Global Holdings LLC.'
p3550
aS'Major retailers including Macy\xe2\x80\x99s Inc ( ) and Sears Holding Corp ( ) have closed hundreds of locations as they struggle to compete discounters such as Wal-Mart Stores Inc ( ) and Amazon.com Inc ( ).'
p3551
aS'Amazon\xe2\x80\x99s recent acquisition of high-end grocer Whole Foods Markets Inc stirred speculation that the online giant will use its pricing power and huge reach among U.S. consumers to go after market share of traditional brick-and-mortar grocers.'
p3552
aS'Toys \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us is the second-largest toy seller in the United States behind Amazon, according to consulting firm Kloster Trading Corp.'
p3553
aS'"What they have going for them is they are the last major player in their market," said David Berliner, a partner and restructuring specialist with BDO Consulting.'
p3554
aS'"The vendors don\xe2\x80\x99t want to see them fail, so I think they have a good opportunity to survive".'
p3555
aS'Toys \xe2\x80\x98R\xe2\x80\x99 Us filed the petition in the U.S. Bankruptcy Court for the Eastern District of Virginia in Richmond, Virginia.'
