aS'The idea of an unbroken, unchanged culture has a flip side that has always animated racists.'
p4863
aS'It was once used to portray Indigenous Australians, and other nonwhite races, as primitive and incapable of development.'
p4864
aS'Likewise with another common claim: that Indigenous people have a special attachment to the land and a unique form of ecological wisdom.'
p4865
aS'This, too, draws on an old racist trope, a reworking of the "noble savage" myth.'
p4866
aS'The fact that in contemporary debates such ideas are deployed in support, rather than denial, of Indigenous rights does not make them more palatable.'
