aS'Graham-Cassidy would further cripple Medicaid by putting a per-person cap on what the federal government spends on the program.'
p5466
aS'Under current law, federal spending increases automatically to keep up with the rise in medical costs; a per-capita cap would leave governors, who are ultimately in charge of administering Medicaid, in the unenviable position of denying care to poor and older Americans.'
