aS'On Sept. 1 Kenya\xe2\x80\x99s Supreme Court made the unprecedented decision to nullify the results of the country\xe2\x80\x99s Aug. 8 presidential election,   the victory by incumbent President Uhuru Kenyatta and calling for fresh elections in 60 days.'
p5568
aS'A decade after the 2007 presidential election was followed by violence that killed more than 1,000 people, it is a historic moment not just for Kenya but also for the continent, and guarantees greater global attention on the country this fall.'
p5569
aS'In response to a   filed by the opposition leader and former prime minister Raila Odinga, the court ruled the election was not conducted in accordance with the Constitution, citing "illegalities and irregularities" committed by Kenya\xe2\x80\x99s election commission.'
p5570
aS'The court ruling didn\xe2\x80\x99t contradict the   of the Carter Center, whose team we led, or those of other observer missions, including the European Union and African Union, whose findings were broadly similar.'
p5571
aS'Multiple media reports suggested inaccurately that we and other international observers had declared the election free and fair.'
p5572
aS'Our preliminary   two days after the election insisted that the tallying process was in progress and that an overall assessment could be provided only after the process was complete.'
p5573
aS'Although our observers had noted isolated instances of procedural irregularities in voting and counting, these did not appear to affect the integrity of those processes, which had functioned relatively smoothly.'
p5574
aS'We also indicated that the electronic transmission of results proved unreliable, with electronic scans of results forms not arriving as planned at constituency-level tally centers, where the results were tabulated As a backup measure, the election commission instructed the constituency centers to rely instead on the   results forms to tally the official results.'
p5575
aS'We noted that the paper-based backup system, if implemented properly, would allow verification of the ballots cast and that agents of political parties had been at most stations and received copies they could crosscheck with the official results.'
p5576
aS'At the time, there had been sporadic outbreaks of violence, followed by reports of excessive use of force by the government.'
p5577
aS'Mr. Odinga argued he wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t take his case to court but would instead let it play out in "the court of   opinion".'
p5578
aS'It reminded us of the 2007 elections when Mr. Odinga lost to President Mwai Kibaki and mass violence followed.'
p5579
aS'Our major exhortation \xe2\x80\x94 which angered some at the time \xe2\x80\x94 was that all aggrieved parties should pursue their disputes in the courts, not the streets.'
p5580
aS'We and the other international observer mission leaders pressed, both publicly and in private meetings with leaders, for claims of misconduct and fraud to be fully investigated, rather than reduced to rhetoric and innuendo.'
p5581
aS'Many in the media, including this newspaper\xe2\x80\x99s editorial page, have wondered whether the court ruling has exposed flaws in election observation missions.'
p5582
aS'What they misunderstand is that our early reports were preliminary, covering only the voting and counting stages, not the critical postelection phases of tabulation and dispute resolution that were still ongoing.'
p5583
aS'They also overlook that international observers led the call for candidates to take their disputes to the courts.'
p5584
aS'That happened, and that is a good thing.'
p5585
aS'Our observers remain in Kenya and continue their monitoring work.'
p5586
aS'A final comprehensive report will be completed after the conclusion of the new election and the resolution of any petitions.'
p5587
aS'In its electoral petition, Mr. Odinga\xe2\x80\x99s opposition coalition claimed that the election commission did not follow proper procedures in tabulating and announcing final results and that there were inaccuracies in the forms recording polling station results and constituency-level tallying.'
p5588
aS'They also claimed that the commission\xe2\x80\x99s servers were hacked to manipulate results.'
p5589
aS'The election commission has confirmed that there were attempts to hack its servers, but officials deny that any malfeasance occurred.'
p5590
aS'The Supreme Court has not yet said what parts of Mr. Odinga\xe2\x80\x99s challenge it agreed with.'
p5591
aS'Until it releases a detailed explanation, it is impossible to know the precise basis for its decision and for the commission to plan corrective actions.'
p5592
aS'The court should be commended for affording due process and a transparent review, bolstering public confidence in its independence and reducing tensions across the country.'
p5593
aS'The election commission has announced that the new election will be held on Oct. 17.'
p5594
aS'It is critical that the process be conducted flawlessly.'
p5595
aS'The government needs to provide the financial resources to make that possible and take steps to ensure the security of the commissioners, candidates and voters.'
p5596
aS'Initially, President Kenyatta spoke about respecting the court\xe2\x80\x99s decision, but sadly, in subsequent statements, he   the judges as "crooks" and vowed to "fix" the court if re-elected.'
p5597
aS'All Kenyans, especially its political leaders, need to act responsibly and ensure that the new electoral process is peaceful.'
p5598
aS'This is a critical time for Kenya.'
p5599
aS'Democracy is hard work requiring many hands.'
p5600
aS'The court\xe2\x80\x99s historic decision means the world will be watching this race even more closely, and international election monitors must as well.'
p5601
aS'A transparent, credible and peaceful process will affirm the power of Kenya\xe2\x80\x99s democracy \xe2\x80\x94 after its court system has already affirmed the strength of its institutions.'
