aS'I countered.'
p6342
aS'"I trust his judgment," the man said.'
p6343
aS'They trusted his judgment and on Election Day they trusted Mr. Trump more than they trusted any of us.'
p6344
aS'That\xe2\x80\x99s why when members of the media pronounced his candidacy dead, his supporters knew the opposite was true.'
p6345
aS'It was never more alive.'
p6346
aS'Maybe that has changed.'
p6347
aS'I don\xe2\x80\x99t know.'
p6348
aS'Nobody does.'
p6349
aS'The building blocks of political life are too complex to predict, too unstable to rely on.'
p6350
aS'But I do know what political devotion looks like, and I do know what happens when you choose to discount it.'
