aS'Classmates at Freeman High School in the tiny town of Rockford, south of Spokane, knew about the videos.'
p9681
aS'Junior Paul Fricke told The Spokesman-Review newspaper (  ) that "we knew he had an assault rifle, because he uses it in his YouTube videos".'
p9682
aS'In one, the suspect and a friend display several guns, including what appear to be airsoft weapons and one actual rifle, and act out a scenario where they search for an imaginary neighborhood drug dealer.'
p9683
aS'Another student described the suspect as obsessed with previous school shootings.'
