aS'Not to worry, I have good news: Vacation research \xe2\x80\x94 yes, there is such a thing \xe2\x80\x94 shows that beyond a week or two away from work, more time off isn\xe2\x80\x99t going to make you happier or calmer or produce more lasting gains of another sort.'
p10266
aS'For example, in a 2012   in the Netherlands, in which the duration of the participants\xe2\x80\x99 vacations ranged from 14 to 35 days, researchers found that subjective measures of health and wellness shot up rapidly at the start of the break and then peaked by Day 8.'
p10267
aS'Sadly, these positive vacation effects evaporated after just one day back at work.'
