aS'The Constitution gives the president the power to choose federal judges, but only with the "advice and consent" of the Senate.'
p11218
aS'In an earlier era of relative comity and good faith, the blue-slip tradition may have helped to ensure that advice was considered.'
p11219
aS'But in this toxic, hyperpartisan age, there\xe2\x80\x99s no simple way to force a president to listen.'
p11220
aS'And that is not a minor matter.'
