aS'TOKYO \xe2\x80\x94 The whole world confronts an unprecedented, grave and imminent threat from North Korea.'
p11423
aS'On Sept. 3, the regime carried out a reprehensible nuclear test.'
p11424
aS'Late last week, it launched a ballistic missile over my country, Japan, only two weeks after a similar missile launch.'
p11425
aS'By repeatedly testing missiles \xe2\x80\x94 in violation of United Nations Security Council resolutions \xe2\x80\x94 Pyongyang has shown its reach now extends to the United States and Europe.'
p11426
aS'North Korea\xe2\x80\x99s actions are an outright challenge to the international community.'
p11427
aS'On Sept. 11, the United Nations Security Council unanimously adopted a resolution on a new round of strict sanctions that restrict member states from selling oil to the North, ban North Korean textile exports and ban member states from authorizing North Koreans to work abroad.'
p11428
aS'They are an important step, but the leadership in Pyongyang has consistently ignored previous resolutions.'
p11429
aS'The international community must stay united and enforce the sanctions.'
p11430
aS'Here in northeast Asia, the North Korean threat has been real for more than a quarter-century.'
p11431
aS'We face the threat of missiles \xe2\x80\x94 short and medium range \xe2\x80\x94 together with the possibility of chemical weapons attacks.'
p11432
aS'North Korea has targeted Japan in particular by abducting many innocent Japanese citizens, including a 13-year-old girl who was abducted in 1977.'
p11433
aS'Most of them have been held in North Korea since the 1970s and 1980s.'
p11434
aS'Everyone aspires to a peaceful solution to these challenges.'
p11435
aS'And global solidarity is of utmost importance.'
p11436
aS'Still, prioritizing diplomacy and emphasizing the importance of dialogue will not work with North Korea.'
p11437
aS'History shows that concerted pressure by the entire international community is essential.'
p11438
aS'In the early 1990s, North Korea\xe2\x80\x99s announcement to withdraw from the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty and the International Atomic Energy Agency was a wake-up call.'
p11439
aS'In response, Japan, the United States and South Korea engaged in dialogue with North Korea and agreed to construct two light-water reactors and to provide heavy fuel oil in exchange for freezing and ultimately dismantling its nuclear program.'
p11440
aS'Japan, the United States and South Korea shouldered most of the financial burden, with the cooperation of Europe and other Asian countries.'
p11441
aS'We know what happened next: Several years after the heavy fuel oil was delivered and construction started on the light-water reactors, North Korea admitted to having a uranium enrichment program in violation of the agreement.'
p11442
aS'By the end of 2002, North Korea expelled I.A.E.A. inspectors, followed by an official withdrawal from the NPT in 2003.'
p11443
aS'China and Russia then joined Japan, the United States and South Korea to create the six-party talks with the North.'
p11444
aS'Pyongyang again agreed to the verifiable denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula.'
p11445
aS'But instead, it declared itself a nuclear power in 2005 and carried out a nuclear test in 2006.'
p11446
aS'The five countries\xe2\x80\x99 attempt to solve the problem through dialogue failed.'
p11447
aS'In short, while the international community provided North Korea with sanctions relief and support as "compensation" for its pledges, the regime ignored most of its commitments.'
p11448
aS'Considering this history and its continuing missile launches and nuclear tests, more dialogue with North Korea would be a dead end.'
p11449
aS'Pyongyang would see more talks as proof that other countries succumbed to the success of its missile launches and nuclear tests.'
p11450
aS'Now is the time to exert the utmost pressure on the North.'
p11451
aS'There should be no more delays.'
p11452
aS'How could North Korea relentlessly pursue missile development and nuclear tests over almost half a century?'
p11453
aS'How could North Korea, under successive United Nations sanctions for a decade, acquire enormous resources to obtain crude materials, components and powerful engines?'
p11454
aS'Statistics show that there are countries, mainly in Asia, that continue trading with North Korea; and for some, as recently as in 2016, their trade even exceeded that of the previous year.'
p11455
aS'According to the United Nations, foreign-made parts have been used in North Korea\xe2\x80\x99s ballistic missiles.'
p11456
aS'There are countries buying products and services from North Korea or accepting its workers.'
p11457
aS'Front companies established in Asia enable North Korea access to foreign currencies.'
p11458
aS'Japan has responded by reaffirming the ironclad Japan-United States alliance, and Japan has coordinated in lock step with the United States and South Korea.'
p11459
aS'I firmly support the United States position that all options are on the table.'
p11460
aS'As a response to the latest nuclear test, I value the swift and unanimous adoption of Security Council Resolution 2375 on Sept. 11, which puts significantly tougher sanctions on North Korea.'
p11461
aS'But I stress that we must not be simply complacent with the adoption of these sanctions.'
p11462
aS'We must thoroughly enforce the successive resolutions in order to prevent North Korea from obtaining the goods, technologies, funds and people to further develop its missiles and nuclear program.'
p11463
aS'North Korea poses a serious threat and challenge to our world, and its actions flout the international nonproliferation regime.'
p11464
aS'As swiftly as possible, we must make North Korea end its provocations, abandon its nuclear and ballistic missile development, and return the abductees in North Korea to their homes.'
p11465
aS'Solidarity and concerted effort among the international community, together with the effective role of the United Nations, are more vital than ever.'
