aS'Yet Graham-Cassidy makes more sweeping changes by turning money currently used on insurance subsidies and the Medicaid expansion into block grants to states.'
p15681
aS'This change would give states more flexibility to design their own health care systems.'
p15682
aS'The prospects for Graham-Cassidy remain in doubt, but the battle over whether states or the federal government should have more control over health care policy will remain no matter what happens in the coming weeks.'
p15683
aS'There is a strong case for a system that takes a less Washington-centric approach to health care and turns more decisions over to the states.'
