aS'When distant lawmakers and unelected bureaucrats are in a position to make decisions that have enormous implications for the entire nation, the stakes of any decision become much higher.'
p15687
aS'This is especially true when it comes to health care policy, which has the most personal and life-altering effects on individuals and their families.'
