aS'On Monday, former New York Congressman Anthony Weiner was sentenced to 21 months in prison for having lewd exchanges with a 15-year-old girl on Skype and Snapchat.'
p15972
aS'The sentencing was just the latest act in Mr. Weiner\xe2\x80\x99s nightmarish downfall fueled by his compulsive sexting habit.'
p15973
aS'Mr. Weiner cried as he pleaded guilty to one count of transferring obscene material to a minor, a crime that carried up to 10 years in prison.'
p15974
aS'"I acted not only unlawfully but immorally, and if I had done the right thing, I would not be standing before you today," he told Judge Denise L. Cote in Manhattan.'
p15975
aS'"I was a very sick man for a very long time," he said.'
p15976
aS'Indeed, his behavior fits a commonly understood definition of addiction, which is persistent engagement in a behavior despite negative consequences.'
p15977
aS'And those consequences were epic \xe2\x80\x94 loss of his congressional office in 2011, the implosion of his mayoral bid in 2013, public humiliation, the dissolution of his marriage and accusations of jeopardizing Hillary Clinton\xe2\x80\x99s presidential bid.'
p15978
aS'"I\xe2\x80\x99ve had a disease but I have no excuse," he continued.'
p15979
aS'"I accept complete and total responsibility for my crime. I was the adult".'
p15980
aS'In admitting this, Mr. Weiner captured an important distinction that has been lost in our culture, which tends to over-pathologize problematic behavior.'
p15981
aS'He didn\xe2\x80\x99t blame his "disease".'
p15982
aS'He knows that there is a difference between having a compulsion and acting on it.'
p15983
aS'But there is an idea bigger than just controlling one\xe2\x80\x99s impulses.'
p15984
aS'It\xe2\x80\x99s what legal scholars and philosophers call "diachronous responsibility".'
p15985
aS'Consider the drunken driver.'
p15986
aS'Once he is tanked up on whisky and heading to his car to drive home, it is unrealistic to expect that he will instead amble to the closest Starbucks to sober up or call someone to drive him home.'
p15987
aS'A cycle has been tripped and the odds are that he\xe2\x80\x99ll drive home intoxicated.'
p15988
aS'If he kills someone, it\xe2\x80\x99s no excuse.'
p15989
aS'That\xe2\x80\x99s because he had ample opportunity to be responsible: When he was sober and walked into the bar.'
p15990
aS'That was his first mistake, and a totally avoidable one.'
p15991
aS'According to Stephen Morse, a law professor at the University of Pennsylvania, a person can be responsible for the ultimate harm, even if that person is somehow not responsible at the moment of committing an act, as long as three conditions are met: He must a) be responsible at other times, b) know or should know that he is at risk of causing those harms in a non-responsible state, and c) fail to take reasonable steps to prevent the harm from arising.'
p15992
aS'Mr. Weiner is three for three on the diachronous-responsibility test.'
p15993
aS'First, he is responsible at other times.'
p15994
aS'Clearly, Mr. Weiner knew enough not to sext in front of his wife.'
p15995
aS'Second, he knew or should have known that he was at risk of causing those harms in a non-responsible state.'
p15996
aS'Mr. Weiner is an intelligent man who had watched his life crumble years before the offense.'
p15997
aS'And third, he failed to take reasonable steps to prevent the harm from arising.'
p15998
aS'Addicts, pedophiles and others are in the same situation when they are not "overwhelmed" by their desires, Mr. Morse told me.'
p15999
aS'"They need to be held accountable if they don\xe2\x80\x99t take steps to tie themselves to the mast to avoid being overwhelmed".'
p16000
aS'The mast reference here is to Ulysses, literature\xe2\x80\x99s most famous subject of temptation, who tied himself to the mast of his ship to keep from submitting to the sirens\xe2\x80\x99 call.'
p16001
aS'Ulysses\xe2\x80\x99s self-regulation led the political philosopher Jon Elster to coin the idea of Ulysses contracts.'
p16002
aS'For example, a gambler might tell his local casino to bar him from entering in the first place.'
p16003
aS'In Mr. Weiner\xe2\x80\x99s case, that contract might mean putting parental controls on his own laptop, or even not owning a smartphone.'
