p16225
aS'It begins to feel as if a small war is about to break out between the soldiers.'
p16226
aS'A strange sight follows: After the flag-lowering ritual is over, Indians and Pakistanis rush toward the border gates.'
p16227
aS'They stare at one another curiously.'
p16228
aS'A sense of rivalry isn\xe2\x80\x99t seen among them.'
p16229
aS'A "you are just like us" sentiment prevails instead.'
p16230
aS'Hoping to see relatives separated from them at the time of the partition in 1947, some Indians and Pakistanis visit the Wagah border time and again.'
p16231
aS'They stand in silence searching for a familiar face on the other side of the border and head home only when the soldiers drive them away.'
p16232
aS'Noor Fatima has brought back these memories.'
p16233
aS'News of her surgery has spread far.'
p16234
aS'What I liked most though was the moral and economic support that Indians extended to her.'
p16235
aS'They have offered her the help that politicians have been unable to give.'
p16236
aS'Noor\xe2\x80\x99s parents have welcomed it graciously.'
p16237
aS'Numerous Indians have donated money to the Dosti Fund (Friendship Fund) that Noor\xe2\x80\x99s father set up to offer aid to poor Indian children.'
p16238
aS'An industrialist, who had lived in Lahore before migrating to India after the partition, has offered 1.2 million rupees.'
p16239
aS'This act of generosity from an Indian Hindu to a fund set up by a Pakistani Muslim demonstrates that the people of the two countries need friendship and harmonious co-existence.'
p16240
aS'At a time when efforts to divide people in the country along lines of caste and religion are underway, ordinary Indians have proved that they won\xe2\x80\x99t let religious difference divide them.'
p16241
aS'The Noor episode clarifies that India\xe2\x80\x99s hostility toward Pakistan is limited to its own security and does not extend to the people of that country or their religion.'
p16242
aS'Indians have ignored the fact that young Noor is from another country.'
p16243
aS'Those Indians who hesitated to come out in support of Muslim victims of the Gujarat violence have stood in support of a Muslim girl from Pakistan.'
p16244
aS'Our hearts don\xe2\x80\x99t have to be filled with hatred.'
p16245
aS'Noor made us see that.'
